value.text: Incredible Inventions: Boston's Famous World Exports In case you're wondering, the telephone, invented by Alexander Graham Bell, was created in Boston in 1876; the microwave by Percy Spencer in 1945, and the earliest spreadsheets were invented by Dan Bricklin and Bob Frankston in the 1970s.
